    ) VALUES (1480050, 'Rifampicin', 'Pravastatin', 'Moderate', 'Coadministration with rifampin may decrease the oral bioavailability of pravastatin in some patients. The mechanism involves reduced absorption as well as increased first-pass biliary excretion of pravastatin due to rifampin induction of canalicular multispecific organic anion transporter (cMOAT or MRP2), an efflux transporter expressed in the kidney, liver, and intestine and of which pravastatin is a substrate.', NULL, 'Although the effect of rifampin on pravastatin was relatively small compared to that reported for other HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors, the interaction may be clinically significant in some patients.', NULL, 'Although the effect of rifampin on pravastatin was relatively small compared to that reported for other HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors, the interaction may be clinically significant in some patients. Dosage adjustment for pravastatin may be necessary during long-term treatment with rifampin.', 'Others', NULL, NULL, 'Moderate', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', 1767317477);
